column5: Estee Lauder founded her company in 1946 armed with four products and an unshakeable belief: that every woman can be beautiful. Today  more than 60 years later  that simple notion has literally changed the face of the beauty business. Born Josephine Esther Mentzer  EstÃÂ©e Lauder was raised in Corona  Queens  by her Hungarian mother  Rose  and Czech father  Max. The name EstÃÂ©e was a variation on her family nickname  Esty. Always interested in beauty  she was mentored by her uncle  chemist John Schotz  and began her business by selling skin care products to beauty salons and hotels. Perhaps Mrs. Lauder s most important legacy was her belief that in order to make a sale  you must touch the customer. She spent a great deal of time advising customers and teaching Beauty Advisors. EstÃÂ©e Lauder has been a powerhouse in the beauty industry for over 50 years. Today  it is both a cosmetics brand and a multinational company. As one of the largest skincare and makeup organisations in the world  it sets the tone and trends of the beauty marketplace. EstÃÂ©e Lauder offers a full line of cosmetics in several signature collections  including their Pure Colour Collection. Products are available in multiple colours to compliment all skin tones.

column2: Estee Lauder Brush 3 Powder Foundation Brush
column5: CARING FOR YOUR BRUSHCleansing and caring for your makeup brushes will make them last longer-and diminish bacteria build up.Professional makeup brushes should be cleaned once a week.Follow these simple steps: Dampen brush. Apply Estée Lauder Makeup Brush Cleanser to brush hair. (In a pinch you can use baby shampoo or a mild cleanser.) Use your fingers to work into a lather. Rinse thoroughly. Rinse well  then blot excess water with a paper towel and reshape the brush. Lay brush flat to dry. Place at edge of table or counter with bristles pointing out to air dry completely. Avoid drying upright  which can cause bristles to spread and handles to crack.

column5: Meaning of the company name Shiseido: Ã¢ÂÂPraise the virtues of the great Earth  which nurtures new life and brings forth new valuesÃ¢ÂÂ. Having started out as a pharmacy  it wasnÃ¢ÂÂt until 1915 that Shiseido changed direction and committed to the cosmetics industry. The move was masterminded by Shinzo Fukuhara  the third son of Arinobu Fukuhara and the companyÃ¢ÂÂs first president. It was pioneer in introducing cosmetics  makeup or hair care products in the Japanese Market  as the first Japanese toothpaste  the first rice powders for the face with natural colours or the first cosmetic: Eudermine  a lotion that we still have today  although not available in Spain. Since then  Shiseido continued to grow& innovate  using the latest technology in order to get the best products. High importance is given to research  making each product be the result of a very detailed study and lead to a cosmetic discovery. Today  it is the first Japanese cosmetic group-leader in the Asian market and the 4th largest in the world  having presence in 84 countries  15 factories and 12 research centres all over the world  which employ more than 1000 researchers. Important beauty & cosmetics brands such as Carita or Decleor or perfumes as Issey Miyake  Jean Paul Gaultier or Narciso Rodriguez also belong to the Shiseido Group. Hard work has its own rewards  so Shiseido is one of the companies in the beauty sector awarded with the best prizes: IFSCC (International Federation of Societies of Cosmetic Chemists)  considered the Ã¢ÂÂNobelsÃ¢ÂÂ of cosmetics or the prize for being one of the most ethic companies in the whole world. Throughout its history  Shiseido has achieved a perfect balance between East and West  tradition and innovation to help promote and care for the beauty of women  keeping the balance between body and spirit.

Articles   Be a Natural Beauty Get-gorgeous lifestyle tips The key to looking your best is taking care of yourself. Here are a few tips for getting naturally gorgeous--from the inside out. Take H2O to Go Water is essential. If you feel thirsty  youÃ¢ÂÂre already dehydrated. On average  women are advised to drink about 2.5 litres a day  but depending on your level of activity or climate  you may need more. To increase your water intake  keep a bottle with you. YouÃ¢ÂÂll reach for it more often and quickly reap the benefits. From promoting healthy skin to ridding your body of toxins and impurities  water helps keep you looking good and feeling great. Slather on the Sunscreen Skin needs protection from the sunÃ¢ÂÂs rays. The UV index has reached scorching levelsÃ¢ÂÂand not just in the summer monthsÃ¢ÂÂso be sure to wear sunscreen every day. For your face  opt for a lotion or foundation that features SPF 15 to help keep skin protected and wrinkle-free. Remember that SPF allows you to stay in the sun longer without burning  but too much sun exposure can still cause damageÃ¢ÂÂeven if youÃ¢ÂÂre using SPF 50. So when in doubt  cover up. Eat Your Greens Raw fruits and vegetables are rich in vitamins and antioxidants  which benefit your body inside and out. If youÃ¢ÂÂre feeling sleepy in the afternoon  reach for a green apple. It delivers a better boost than a cup of coffee  plus it provides a feeling of fullness without the heavy meal. To reduce bloating  try cucumbers. Just as they remove puffiness from around your eyes  they can nix bloating by filtering out excess water and sodium from your body. To improve your immune system  reach for tomatoes and pomegranates. TheyÃ¢ÂÂre rich in antioxidants  and help to flush out toxins while keeping your immune system strong. Catch Some Zzzzs ThereÃ¢ÂÂs a reason your mother called it beauty rest. Not getting enough sleep creates stress for the body  which shows up on your face. The recommended amount of sleep for adults is eight hours. You can increase the possibility of getting a good nightÃ¢ÂÂs rest by going to sleep at the same time every night. This creates a rhythm for your body to follow. With proper rest  youÃ¢ÂÂll not only maintain a healthy appearance  but also improve your memory and alertness during the day.   Shades Just for You Discover the shades that complement your unique look Fair Skin Lighter colours generally work better on fair skin. Earthy tones or pastels flatter  and mascara should usually be kept to brown or black/brown. Choose light lipstick and peach for your cheeks. Fair-skinned women can also benefit from more daring bursts of colour like thin  dark liner around the eyes  but keep everything else neutral to make them pop. A bright lip looks stunning against a clean  pale face. Medium Skin This skin tone allows for a lot of colour variety. You can easily wear rich shades and deep earth tones or colours such as hunter green and plum to accentuate your eyes. Coral shades look best on cheeks and bronzing powder can enhance your natural tone. Medium skin tones have a versatile lip palette  so colour can range from sheer pink by day to deep red by night. Dark Skin Dark skin tones allow you to opt for one of two extremes: dark and deep or light and shimmery. Neutral shades  dark purple  and dark blue are ideal for highlighting eyes.ÃÂ  Metallic shades in silver  copper  and even gold  although very different from darker colours  work to make your eyes the focus of your face. Cheek tones should be kept close to your natural tone. Dark lip colours such as berries  caramels  and reds work well for this skin tone. Olive Skin Neutral shades and dark purples and greens work well to outline your eyes because although your skin may be light  it offers the warmth these colours require. Cheeks should be highlighted with bronzing powder  burgundy  or plum blush. Similar colours like berries  plums  and neutrals also bring out your lips. True reds should be avoided as they often clash with an olive skin tone. To add depth  choose a richer hue to blend from the pupil to the outer edge of the eye. Line eyes with black-brown pencil within the lash  line to make them look rich and thick. Create doe-like lashes by curling and using Voluminous Mascara to extend them to their full potential. Remember to do both upper and lower lashes. Dust Glam Bronze Loose Powder Highlighter across cheeks  forehead  and chin to get gorgeous shimmer all over and that signature BeyoncÃÂ© Glow. Finish with a Colour RicheÃÂ® Sheers for seductive lips that shine. Diane: Forever confident and always original  Diane KeatonÃ¢ÂÂs look is beautifully effortless.
